Running Instructions:
	

Notes and Assumptions:


Accessories: (for optional Arduino 4-button game controller)
	- Arduino Mega Board (AMG)
	- Pushbutton (4)
	- USB A-micro cable


Wiring instructions:
	
	*****UPDATE THESE INSTRUCTIONS*****

	Pin 6 <--> increment pushbutton lead|other lead <--> GND
	Pin 7 <--> decrement pushbutton lead|other lead <--> GND
	Pin 9 <--> LED 0 (red) long lead|short lead <--> 560 Ohm resistor <--> GND
	Pin 10<--> LED 1 (red) long lead|short lead <--> 560 Ohm resistor <--> GND
	Pin 11<--> LED 2 (grn) long lead|short lead <--> 560 Ohm resistor <--> GND
	Pin 12<--> LED 3 (red) long lead|short lead <--> 560 Ohm resistor <--> GND
	Pin 13<--> LED 4 (red) long lead|short lead <--> 560 Ohm resistor <--> GND
	
	Pin 5V  <--> Power  (+) rail on breadboard
	Pin GND <--> Ground (-) rail on breadboard


Extra Features:
	Game built with pygame:
	https://www.pygame.org/docs/

	Serial interfacing between python and connected Arduino via pyserial:
	https://pythonhosted.org/pyserial/

	Multithreading for background serial processing and pygame event posting:
	https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15538287/can-i-add-pygame-events-from-a-second-thread
	https://stackoverflow.com/questions/18018033/how-to-stop-a-looping-thread-in-python

	Static Properties and Methods:
	https://stackoverflow.com/questions/68645/are-static-class-variables-possible
	https://stackoverflow.com/questions/735975/static-methods-in-python
	
	class inheritance with super:
	https://www.pythonforbeginners.com/super/working-python-super-function








